The troops of 32 Artillery Brigade said it rescued 10 persons who were kidnapped  from a forest at Erio - Efon Alaaye road in Ekiti State. A statement by the Assistant Director, Army Public Relations, Ojo Adenegan, yesterday in Ado Ekiti said the arrest was in continuation of its clearance operations at various flashpoints and blackspots in the state. The statement said the victims were kidnapped on their way to Ado Ekiti from Efon Alaaye in two commercial buses at different points. He added, “the information got to our troops who were on intensive patrol where they quickly responded by combing the forest and had exchange of fire between own troops and the kidnappers who later fled as a result of firepower. The ten victims who were held hostage were rescued safely without any injury.” He said the police from Efon Alaaye also participated in the operation, adding that the victims had been handed over to the police headquarters in the state.